olive oil
4 clove garlic
2 tin cannellini beans
1 Onion
2 tbs white wine vinegar
2 tsp brown sugar
1 lemon
1 packet thyme
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
¼ tsp pepper
¼ tsp salt
¼ cup water

• Boil the kettle. Peel garlic cloves. Drain cannellini beans.
• Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water and a generous pinch
of salt.
• Cook cannellini beans and garlic in the boiling water, over high heat, until softened, 6-7 minutes.
• Drain, allow to cool slightly and transfer to a food processor.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice onion.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook onion, stirring regularly until softened, 5-6 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium. Add the white wine vinegar, brown sugar, a pinch of salt and splash of water and mix well. Cook until sticky, 3-5 minutes.
• Transfer to food processor with cannellini beans.

• Meanwhile, zest lemon to get a pinch and slice into wedges. Pick thyme
leaves (reserve a pinch for garnish!).
• To the food processor, add grated parmesan cheese, juice of the lemon, thyme, the pepper, salt, water and a generous drizzle of olive oil. Blitz until smooth.

• Transfer to a serving bowl, sprinkle over lemon zest, reserved thyme leaves and season with pepper. Drizzle over olive oil to serve. Enjoy!